&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Gastroenterology Team are recruiting a Clinical Fellow (FY2 Level) on a permanent basis.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Gastroenterology firm is a general medical firm with an interest in Gastroenterology based on the Eleanor Hobbs ward at Southend University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust. You will have excellent opportunities to see and manage a variety of general medical and Gastroenterology cases. We have an active endoscopy and ERCP unit and you will have the opportunity to gain experience in managing GI disorders such as GI bleeds, liver disease and paracentesis, as well as observation sessions in the endoscopy unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Medicine Directorate offers a personalised supportive induction programme for all newly appointed candidates. Through our induction programme, we ensure that all new team members feel integrated and supported. We include regular reviews and opportunities to flex the induction programme as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please review the attached job description and person specification as well as our Medicine Directorate and Trust information documents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameVictoria JoosteJob titleResource Manager - MedicineEmail addressvictoria.jooste@southend.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
